def: Exempt; protected by inoculation.-- Im*mu"nize, v. t.

A word of unknown origin and signification, formerly used asexpressive of contempt, or when anything said was reject as triflingor impertinent. [Written also tille-vally, tilly-fally, tille-fally,and otherwise.] Shak.
Serious injunction; solemn demand or entreaty. [Obs.] Milton.
An instrument for measuring the forms and angles of salts andcrystals; a goniometer.
Deportment. [Obs.]Stately port and majestical deporture. Speed.
A public square in a city or town.
